page.title: 01DURFORD WOOD & ROGATE COMMON
page.content: The block is sparsley populated apart from the extreme S.W. corner where there are recently-built private and council housing estates. The rising countryside to the north is mainly commercial woodland, both coniferous and chestnut. This covers about one-third of the entire block: the central and southern areas are predominantly used for farming - crops and grazing. Farming provides the main source of employment for the few people working here. The River Rother meanders west to east along low-lying land in the south of the block. It is unused save for occasional anglers and canoists. The buzy A272 Midhurst/Petersfield road intersects the block horizontally and is met in the top north-west corner by the still busier A3 London/Portsmouth road.
